         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">1./7./81. ¶  ¶ I need hardly say, dear Prof. Tate, that in August you will find the spring flowers developed of most species, in December their fruit. A warm mild place like Kang. Isl. or Enc. Bay ¶  ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.07.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Ralph Tate</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Barr Smith Library, University of Adelaide, SA.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1./7./81.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I need hardly say, dear Prof. Tate, that in August you will find the spring flowers developed of most species, in December their fruit. A warm mild place like Kang. Isl. or Enc. Bay<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Kangaroo Island and Encounter Bay, SA. See M to R. Tate, 23 June 1881.</p>
               </note> will have nearly all the terrestrial Orchids &amp; most annuals in bloom during August, which plants will have dried up in midsummer.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If possible both regions should be traversed both in Spring &amp; Summer. For instance an <name key="Acacia">Acacia</name> in fruit alone cannot be safely named, nor one in flower alone.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The alterations in the mycographic list arise from typographic or writing errors; Berkeley wrote for instance fructuicola, but the root of the word is classically fructi not fructui.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was delighted, that my namesake on the turf<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">A racehorse owned by Thomas Elder named 'Baron von Mueller'. See Dwyer (1996).</p>
               </note> brought no discredit on his sponsor, and hope he will sustain his renommée<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">reputation.</p>
               </note> also in the great Champion-Race of Melbourne<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i<seg style="">.e. the Melbourne </seg>Cup meeting, 1 November 1881, where 'Baron von Mueller' ran in the last race of the day, the Yan Yean Stakes handicap, which it won by a short neck from the favourite, surviving a protest (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Age</seg> (Melbourne), 2 November 1881, p. 6).</p>
               </note> on Prince of Wales Birthday next.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">You named <name key="Schoenus%20Tepperi">Schoenus Tepperi</name> quite correctly from the new locality.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Acacia">Acacia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Schoenus%20Tepperi">Schoenus Tepperi</name>
            </p>
